{{Infobox model | name = Rebecca da Costa | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1984|5}} | birth_place = [[Recife]], [[Pernambuco]], Brazil | nationality = Brazilian | religion = | occupation = Actress, model | height = {{convert|1.80|m|ftin|abbr=on}} | haircolor = Brown | eyecolor = Brown | spouse = | children = | agency = | yearsactive = 2009-present | website = {{URL|http://www.rebeccadacosta.com/}} }}
'''Rebecca da Costa''' (born May 9, 1984) is a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] actress and model. She has worked with actors including [[Robert De Niro]], [[John Cusack]] and [[Val Kilmer]].
==Early life and modelling career== Da Costa was born in Recife, capital of [[Pernambuco]]. She was educated at the Colégio [[Rui Barbosa]],<ref name=nol/> where she directed, wrote and starred in amateur theatrical productions.<ref name=nol/><ref name=pum/><ref name=sim/> Of her physique she said, "Until I was 17 I thought I was ugly. I was very tall. At 13, I was 5'11″. I come from a part in Brazil where the average height for women is 5'3″. It wasn't fun at all to be the tallest one in school."<ref name= blot/> Aged 14 she won a modeling contest in Recife and says, "It was amazing to see other girls like me—skinny, tall, different. That's when I started to get comfortable in my own skin, and by 17 I started to find my identity."<ref name= blot/> At 14<ref name=pum>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Kam|title=From the Runway to the Red Carpet!|url=http://pittsburghurbanmedia.com/From-the-Runway-to-the-Red-Carpet-PUM-One-on-One-with-Rebecca-Da-Costa/|website=Pittsburgh Urban Media|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref> she left home for [[São Paulo]]<ref name=sim/> when she was taken on by [[Elite Model Management]]<ref name=starpulse>{{cite web|last1=McGrath|first1=Lisa|title=Rebecca Da Costa: Getting To Know The Star Of 'Motel' And 'Breaking At The Edge'|url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/Lisa_McGrath/2013/03/22/rebecca_da_costa_getting_to_know_the_s|website=Star Pulse|accessdate=11 August 2014}}</ref> and began a ten-year modelling career. She is 5&nbsp;ft 11 in (1.80 m) tall.<ref name=sim/> At age 16 she was invited to work at the [[Milan Fashion Week]]<ref name=pum/><ref name=sim/> and moved to Italy, working for [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], [[Moschino]], [[Armani]], [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]], [[DKNY]], [[Missoni]], [[Hugo Boss]] and [[Escada]],<ref name=nol/> and was the face of campaigns for [[Swarovski]],<ref name=nol/> [[Nokia]], [[L'Oreal]], [[Chopard]]<ref name=pum/> and [[Kellogg's]].{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}
== Filmography == {| class="wikitable" |- style="text-align:center;" ! style="background:#B0C4DE;" | Year ! style="background:#B0C4DE;" | Film ! style="background:#B0C4DE;" | Role ! style="background:#B0C4DE;" | Notes |- | rowspan="2" | 2010 || ''[[Trick of the Witch]]'' || Anabella || |- | ''[[Treasure of the Black Jaguar]]'' || Waitress || |- | rowspan="2" | 2011 || ''[[L.A., I Hate You]]'' || Natasha || |- | ''[[Freerunner (film)|Freerunner]]'' || Chelsea || |- | rowspan="2" | 2012 || ''[[Mine Games]]'' || Rose || |- | ''[[Seven Below]]'' || Courtney || |- | rowspan="1" | 2013 || ''[[Breaking at the Edge]]'' || Bianca Wood || |- | rowspan="1" | 2014 || ''[[The Bag Man]]'' || Rivka || |}
=== Television === ==== TV series ==== * 2009 - ''[[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|Entourage]]'' ([[HBO]]) - Beautiful Woman
==Acting career==
In 2008, Da Costa gave up modelling and moved to the United States to pursue an acting career.<ref name=pum/> She enrolled at the [[HB Studio]] in New York City and made her theater debut alongside [[Brad Garrett]], in [[stand-up comedy]].{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}
In 2009, she made her television debut in an episode of the American [[HBO]] series ''Entourage''.<ref name=pum/> In 2010 she gained a role in the film ''Trick of the Witch'', directed by [[Chris Morrissey (actor/film director)|Chris Morrissey]]. Her first lead film role was in 2011 in the [[independent film|independent]] ''L.A. I Hate You'',<ref name=pum/> starring [[Malcolm McDowell]] and [[William Forsythe (actor)|William Forsythe]],<ref name=starpulse/> and later that year she starred in ''[[Freerunner (film)|Freerunner]]'' alongside [[Sean Faris]]. In 2012, she played in the film ''[[Seven Below]]'', co-starring with [[Val Kilmer]] and [[Ving Rhames]], and in 2013 appeared in ''[[Mine Games]]''.<ref name=pum/>
===''The Bag Man''=== In 2014, Da Costa played in ''[[The Bag Man]]'', "a modern day [[film noir]] shot in [[New Orleans]]",<ref name=nol>{{cite web|last1=Fontana|first1=Christine|title=Rebecca Da Costa: Lovely Leading Lady|url=http://www.livingneworleans.com/?p=9959|website=New Orleans Living|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref> as a [[femme fatale]] who becomes involved in a story of crime and suspense.<ref name=pum/> She co-starred with [[John Cusack]] and [[Robert De Niro]]. The film premiered on February 28, 2014, in New York and Los Angeles.
===''Breaking at the Edge''=== In late 2014 Da Costa was the lead role in ''Breaking at the Edge'' as a [[bipolar disorder|manic–depressive]] pregnant woman who fears for her unborn child's life. The film also features [[Milo Ventimiglia]] and [[Andie MacDowell]]. "When I was shooting it, it was very intense," Da Costa said in February 2014. "I was literally getting crazy."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Johnson|first1=Richard|title=Rebecca Da Costa is your new Latin bombshell|url=http://pagesix.com/2014/02/24/rebecca-da-costa-is-your-new-latin-bombshell/|website=New York Post|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref> She said that preparing for the role she "talked to many psychiatrists. I didn't want to look like I was trying to play crazy."<ref name=blot>{{cite web|last1=Olds|first1=Dorri|title=Exclusive Interview|url=http://theblot.com/exclusive-interview-bombshell-actress-tells-us-deep-sexual-connection-john-cusack-7716042|website=The Blot|accessdate=11 August 2014}}</ref>
==Philanthropy== From her home in Los Angeles, Da Costa works with [http://kidswithautismcan.org Kids with Autism] and [http://commongroundhiv.org Common Ground HIV.]<ref name=pum/>
==Personal life== Da Costa has two brothers. Her father died in 2013.<ref name=sim/> She is fluent in Portuguese, Spanish, Italian and English. She enjoys dancing, reading, cooking Brazilian dishes and writing.<ref name=pum/><ref name=sim/><ref name=nol/> She was in a relationship for many years but broke up in 2013.<ref name=sim>{{cite web|last1=Parker|first1=Melissa|title=Rebecca Da Costa Interview: Breakout Actress Stars Alongside Robert De Niro and John Cusack in Noir-Like Thriller ''The Bag Man''|url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:5gOViRBWEW4J:smashinginterviews.com/interviews/actors/rebecca-da-costa-interview-breakout-actress-stars-alongside-robert-de-niro-and-john-cusack-in-noir-like-thriller-the-bag-man+&cd=8&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk&client=opera|website=Smashing Interviews Magazine|accessdate=10 August 2014}}</ref> Da Costa regularly practices [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]]<ref name=pum/> and says, "It has been a gift to me."<ref name=nol/>
